WHITEHEAD v. UNITED STATES. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. January 16, 1923.) No. 3865. S. S. Sandford and John W. Bull, both of Tampa, Ha., for plaintiff in error. William M. Gober, U. S. Atty., Maynard Ramsey, Asst. U. S. Atty., and Harry W. Reinstine, Sp. Asst. U. S. Atty., all of Jacksonville, Fla.

Before WALKER, BRYAN, and KING, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
